First kit from myself - I was very graciously allowed to wreak havoc on a partially completed creation of Daealis' makings - and the result is this kit.
Designed to be printed in pieces and assembled the old fashioned way, this kit should give you plenty of customisability for your big ghosty bois.
Can be used as a proxy on it's own, or a basis for further conversion.

*Sword removed at request of original components creator - I will sculpt a new one from scratch and update kit soon*

Check out the readme for the credits and links to other creators who's work made this possible :)

The model is provided for free, but even so I would appreciate if you shared the link rather than the model itself, thanks :)

Also, while it's free, please feel welcome to buy me a coffee to help fuel the next one! (link in Bio)

Wraithknight - a fearsome Ghost Warrior, driven by the twin pilots within, set to annihilate any enemy of the Aeldari that dares to cross its path. An overpowering presence on the battlefield, armed with colossal energy cannons, this towering construct can discharge fiery destruction.

Its height is about 22cm from the bottom of the feet to the top of the head.
It weighs about 150g.

ALL PARTS FOR THIS KNIGHT ARE CUSTOM MADE AND HAVE DIFFERENT JOINTS AND SOCKETS IN COMPARISON TO REAL ONE.

All files are hollowed except Torso Gun, Hand Gun, and Torso Back parts.
All files are inspected in Meshmixer and ready for 3d printing.

Be free to send a request for a commission for it and I'll see what I can do. 

If you appreciate this work and would like to see more Tip :)
And happy printing.

Having trouble with downloading, check here: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/161fNu0mhz2sSiPwtt2M-lv22jiQvy5s5

Copyright infringement is not intended. All parts are created freehand in 3d modeling software, no copyrighted product had been scanned or copied in any way.
These models are for personal use as proxies and should never be sold. If it causes copyright issues, I will remove it.

This is simply a collection of things mostly from other people that I used to upgrade an old Eldar Wraithlord to Seer status.

I repaired the elements from jimjimjimmyjim's wraithseer to make them more easily printable as they caused issues with my slicer.

It is all non-scaled and you need to fit it to your needs in your splicer (Cura worked pretty good for that purpose e.g. to inlay the rune into base and Shield)
- Spear is too large (lenght advis 130-140 mm)
- The Base is to high and to small (advise: diameter 65mm - height 8 mm)
- The Shield (longest length 25-30 mm)
- The gun is also too large (overall length should ideally be around 65mm --> scaling the canon trippel to a height of 25-30mm worked for me)
- rune and back is up to your liking.
